 for OSX or Windows.\r\n\r\n@wwoodall suggested the python library [psutil](http://code.google.com/p/psutil/), which is portable to Linux, OSX and Windows. Since it's relatively small, we could consider including it in the `test/performance` folder.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/de1302de781064de8b4fa3a078f20f11852ca823/test/performance/RAMLibrary.hh?at=default\" rel=\"nofollow\">test/performance/RAMLibrary.hh</a> is currently used for testing memory usage in the performance tests, but it is not portable, as it currently parses <code>/proc/meminfo</code> for Linux, but this is not available for OSX or Windows.</p>\n<p>@wwoodall suggested the python library <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://code.google.com/p/psutil/\" rel=\"nofollow\">psutil</a>, which is portable to Linux, OSX and Windows. Since it's relatively small, we could consider including it in the <code>test/performance</code> folder.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-08-13T17:45:59.220208+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:23:27.142517+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 802}